# D8TAOPS Sales Intelligence Platform

## What This Is
A 4-step sales tool for D8TAOPS Sales Leaders (SLs).
SL enters industry + use case → gets tailored D8:PLATFORM agent config,
KCU-calibrated ROI model, and ready-to-use sales materials
(email, talking points, exec summary, ROI card, slide deck outline).

## Tech Stack
- React + Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) — 4 AI calls total
- No backend. No database. No auth. No Stripe.
- Deploy: Vercel

## Brand
- Font: IBM Plex Sans (Google Fonts)
- Navy: #1B3A5C
- Blue: #0477BF
- BG: #EFF2F6
- White: #FFFFFF
- Border: #DDE2EA

## App Structure
4 steps, all state in React memory (no persistence):
1. Target — input form (industry + use case required, company/contact optional)
2. Solution — AI-generated agent config, pain points, benchmarks
3. ROI Model — KCU-calibrated calculator with 6 sliders + KCU bridge block
4. Export — 5 tabs: Email, Talking Points, Exec Summary, ROI Card, Slide Deck

## ROI Formula (KCU-calibrated — do not change)
annualCycles = vol × 12
totalHrsPerCycle = hrs × staff
aiHrs = totalHrsPerCycle × 0.03        // 97% reduction
hrsSaved = (totalHrsPerCycle - aiHrs) × annualCycles
timeSave = hrsSaved × rate
errSave = annualCycles × max(0, errPct/100 - 0.005) × errCost
total = timeSave + errSave
impl = max(65000, min(280000, vol × 45 + 40000))
roiPct = ((total - impl) / impl) × 100
payback = ceil(impl / (total / 12))

## Claude API Calls
Endpoint: POST https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
Headers: Content-Type: application/json (no API key — injected by platform)
Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514
max_tokens: 1000
All responses: JSON only. Strip ```json fences before parsing.

Calls:
1. SYS_RESEARCH — on "Analyze" button. Returns: companyProfile, painPoints, benchmarks, opportunities
2. SYS_SOLUTION — immediately after research. Returns: headline, sub, agents[], workflow, outcomes[], advantage
3. SYS_EXPORT — on "Generate Materials" button. Returns: emailSubject, emailBody, talkingPoints[], execSummary, roiLine
4. SYS_DECK — on "Generate Deck" button (on-demand). Returns: slides[]

Exact system prompt text is in REFERENCE_prototype.jsx — use it verbatim.

